This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, moreÂ children and adolescents, particularly the most vulnerable, benefitÂ from more effective, quality, gender-sensitive, preventive, and responsive child protection system, and live in communities that better protect children from violence.

description.narrative: Follow-up assessments of 730 (488 boys, 242 girls) of 1,869 children, disengaged from the MILF, found that none have re-associated with armed groups. Child Rights focused religious sermons reached 600,000 resulting;to a deeper understanding of child protection and;child rights;as evidenced by;pre-test and post-test results and feedback; via quad-media channels. Approximately 8,000 adolescents and U-reporters participated in;U-report polls identifying;key issues. Such were formally presented;to ;BARMM leaders and development partners for their action.;A;new Children’s Code was drafted and a shock responsive social protection system was integrated in the emergency cash transfer mechanism. Provision of MHPSS benefitted 8,160 children, parents and caregivers.; | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:23/12/2021
